\frac{ab}{(a-b)^2} = \frac{1}{x} + \frac{1}{x^2} 
1 + \frac{4}{x} + \frac{4}{x^2} = 1 + 4(\frac{1}{x} + \frac{1}{x^2})
1 + \frac{4}{x} + \frac{4}{x^2} = 1 + \frac{4ab}{(a-b)^2} \\ = \frac{(a-b)^2 + 4ab}{(a-b)^2}\\ = \frac{a^2 + 2ab + b^2}{(a-b)^2}\\ = \frac{(a+b)^2}{(a-b)^2}
\sqrt{1 + \frac{4}{x} + \frac{4}{x^2}} = \pm\frac{a+b}{a-b}
